p: Compounds 392– 393 were also evaluated for growth inhibition activity against newly hatched larvae of H. armigera Hubner. Compounds 392 and 393 showed growth inhibition activities against newly hatched larvae of H. armigera Hubner with the IC 50 values of 150 and 100 µg/mL, respectively. Azadirachtin was used as positive control with the IC 50 value of 25 µg/mL [ 128].
